other_tests.findings: Visualized lung bases are clear with no focal consolidation or pleural effusion. Enhancing region in segment VII of the liver which appears consistent with hemangioma. Hypoattenuating lesion in segment IV of the liver likely represents a simple cyst. Additional small hypodensity within the right lobe of the liver is too small to characterize. The appendix measures approximately 6 mm and is at the upper limits of normal with no surrounding fat stranding. No definite contrast seen within the appendix.
